  <name>ZRAM Configuration Tool</name>
  <summary>Professional ZRAM Compression Utility for Linux</summary>
  
  <description>
    <p>A user-friendly Qt6 GUI application for managing ZRAM (compressed RAM swap) on Linux systems. ZRAM creates a compressed block device in RAM to extend effective memory capacity and improve system responsiveness.</p>
    
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Real-time ZRAM status monitoring (like System Resources)</li>
      <li>Easy configuration with sliders and spinners</li>
      <li>Multiple compression algorithms: zstd, lz4, lzo, lzo-rle, deflate</li>
      <li>Dark/Light theme support</li>
      <li>One-click ZRAM installation</li>
      <li>Multi-distro support: Fedora, Ubuntu, Debian, Arch, openSUSE</li>
      <li>Passwordless sudo for ZRAM operations</li>
      <li>Live memory and swap monitoring</li>
      <li>Desktop integration with applications menu</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
  
